 The Ogun State Government has ordered the immediate sealing of a cashew nut producing company, SONATA Agri International Limited, located at Kilometre 51 along the Lagos-Ibadan expressway, Mowe, for causing air and water pollution in the area. The Director, Compliance Monitoring in the state, Babatunde Lawal, who led a team on an enforcement tour, said the air generated from the plant was posing a great threat to human lives, particularly to pregnant women and children. Reacting to the closure, the companyâ€™s Executive Director, Alhaji Mustapha Lamidi, promised that the company would adhere strictly to the environmental laws of the state if given a second chance.